						<header class="major">
							<h2>Bio</h2>
						</header>
						<p> Welcome to my personal webpage! I am a young data professional with
							two years of experience, both in industry and academia.
							Over the last two years, I have been working as a data scientist at the
							Innocenzo Gasparini Institute for Economic Research
							(IGIER) at Bocconi University. Within this role, I have had the opportunity to
							contribute to empirical research projects at the
							intersection of Economics and Data Science. 
							My academic background includes a Master's degree
							in Economics with a major in Big Data and Business 
						    Analytics from Bocconi University and a Bachelor's
							degree in Economics from the University of Pisa.
							On this webpage, you'll find more details about my
							professional and educational journey, as well as my
							personal interests. If you have any questions or are 
							interested in discussing potential projects, please
							feel free to contact me via email at
							 <a href="mailto:silvia.simonini3@gmail.com">email
							me</a> or connect with me on
							<a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/silvia-simonini-ing-gestionale/">LinkedIn</a>.
							Thank you for visiting!</p>
						<ul class="actions">
 
 						</ul>
 					</section>

				<!-- Two -->
					<section id="two">
						<h2>Research Experience</h2>
						<p>During my Master's studies, I cultivated a strong
							interest in applying quantitative methods and
							computational tools to advance economic research.
							In April 2022, I embarked on an exciting journey as
							a Research Assistant at the Innocenzo Gasparini
							Institute for Economic Research, under the guidance
							of Prof. Francesco Decarolis.
							In this role, I've had the privilege of contributing
							as a data scientist to two large empirical research
							projects. <br>
							
							The first project focuses on the exciting world of Artificial Intelligence and its applications 
							in sponsored search auctions. This work explores
							the effect of algorithmic bidding on digital platforms revenues
							through simulated experiments where bidders employ
							Reinforcement Learning algorithms (<a href="https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=4660391">PDF</a>).<br>
							
							The second project combines Machine Learning and
							econometrics to analyze the network structure
							within the digital advertising industry. It
							investigates the determinants of matching decisions
							within this network, based on a structural econometric
							model for many-to-many matching games.
							A link prediction algorithm is used to retrieve the
							consideration set of advertisers and
							marketing agencies, while NLP techniques are exploited to build some of the
							features that enter the utility function.<br>

							My responsibilities encompass a wide range of tasks, including:
							<ul>
								<li>Development, training, and fine-tuning of AI and ML algorithms.</li>
								<li>Execution of advanced statistical analysis on tabular, text and network data.</li>
								<li>Creation sophisticated data visualizations.</li>
								<li>Scraping data from static and dynamic webpages.</li>
								<li>Cleaning and manipulation of large datasets.</li>
							  </ul>
							Finally, my Master's thesis was an exciting opportunity to engage in original research. 
							Specifically, I conducted an empirical quantitative analysis on the effects of
							recommender systems on demand for songs within the context of music
							streaming platforms. 
						</p>

